\pard\nowidctlpar\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\f1\fs22 - Read the manual (available inline in Steem).\par
- Make regular backups of your steem.ini.\par
In some cases, it can get corrupted, and setting everything up again is a pain. Normally it shouldn't happen anymore in v4, but you never know.\par
- Also back up your shortcuts. Check that you don't define the same shortcut twice.\par
- If Steem SSE crashes on load, it could be due to a corrupted "auto.sts" file, which you are then advised to delete. There is an option to disable resuming the last state on startup.\par
- Try realistic combinations of ST model/TOS (not STE + TOS 1.02, it won't even boot).\par
- Most programs target the colour monitor.\par
- If a program doesn't work, the first things to check are drive speed and ST model. After that, you may change memory size (especially 4MB is trouble with some programs), TOS.\par
- Option 'Low-level 6301 emulation (C1)' is highly recommended for more accurate emulation but it does change the mouse feel (for the better or worse, it depends on personal preference.)\par
- If you're running demos, better check the ST Video option 'Software Overscan'. \par
- If you see dots on some high-colour pictures, adjust the ST Video option 'Shifter Wakeup'. \par
Reminder: this is a problem on real hardware, not an emulation bug. Most demos seem to be compatible with 0, this is the Spectrum 512 standard.\par
- Some patches allow you to pass protection screens of some original games, I only do the easy ones.\par
- For better performance, you may want to close dialog boxes (Options etc.) you don't need.\par

